    "schedule_read": "Union-gather source-boundary compressed-dKV rung. A CTA owns one (token tile, selected window, union-group block, D block), consumes the forward-known active_groups plus token x union-group selected-slot sidecar, recomputes QK, dO.V, softmax probability, and scaled-dP from q/dO/output/lse/kv without materialized P or grad_logits, accumulates dKV[group,D] across the token tile inside the CTA, then emits one global atomic stream per reduced union group. block_d=512 is the preferred gate because it avoids replaying the source-boundary score producer once per D64 tile."
  },
